The Untold Love Story That Inspired Doctor Zhivago  – review","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/sep/18/lara-anna-pasternak-review-the-untold-love-story-that-inspired-doctor-zhivago-olga-ivinskaya-boris","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/books/2016/sep/18/lara-anna-pasternak-review-the-untold-love-story-that-inspired-doctor-zhivago-olga-ivinskaya-boris","fields":{"headline":"Lara: The Untold Love Story That Inspired Doctor Zhivago  – review","standfirst":"Anna Pasternak tale of her great-uncle’s love affair with his muse would make a Hollywood tearjerker in its own right","trailText":"Anna Pasternak tale of her great-uncle’s love affair with his muse would make a Hollywood tearjerker in its own right","byline":"Lucy Scholes","body":"<p>Boris Pasternak’s poetry readings were like pop concerts – a pause from the author spurring “the entire crowd to roar the next line of his verse in unison back at him”. Stalin himself was a fan, ordering the secret police to “leave him in peace, he’s a cloud-dweller”.</p> <p>But someone had to pay for Pasternak’s anti-Soviet novel <a href=\"http://bookshop.theguardian.com/doctor-zhivago.html\" title=\"\"><em>Doctor Zhivago</em></a>, and this was Olga Ivinskaya, the writer’s lover, muse, and the woman upon whom the fictional character of Lara was based. Lara and Yuri’s romance, Anna Pasternak argues, was a “passionate cri de coeur” to the love of Pasternak’s life. Olga was imprisoned twice in Siberian labour camps as a result of their relationship. Pieced together for the first time – family members before the author (Boris’s great-niece) have always denied Olga’s significance – it’s a story with enough romance and suffering to make a moving novel or film in its own right.</p> <p><em>Lara is published by William Collins (£20). </em><a href=\"https://bookshop.theguardian.com/lara-418927.html\" title=\"\"><em>Click here to buy it for £16</em></a><em> </em></p>","wordcount":"176","commentCloseDate":"2016-10-09T06:45:00Z","commentable":"true","productionOffice":"UK","shortUrl":"https://gu.com/p/52zya","thumbnail":"https://media.guim.co.uk/a65bc0b6264083dd369bb2fd2f59ae3930c502f6/0_233_2797_1678/500.jpg"},"tags":[{"id":"books/biography","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webTitle":"Biography","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/books/biography","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/books/biography","references":[]},{"id":"books/history","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webTitle":"History","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/books/history","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/books/history","references":[]},{"id":"books/boris-pasternak","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webTitle":"Boris Pasternak","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/books/boris-pasternak","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/books/boris-pasternak","references":[]},{"id":"books/books","type":"keyword","sectionId":"books","sectionName":"Books","webTitle":"Books","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/books/books","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/books/books","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","sectionName":"Culture","webTitle":"Culture","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/culture/culture","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/culture/culture","references":[]},{"id":"tracking/commissioningdesk/observer-new-review","type":"tracking","webTitle":"Observer New Review","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/tracking/commissioningdesk/observer-new-review","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/tracking/commissioningdesk/observer-new-review","references":[]},{"id":"tone/reviews","type":"tone","webTitle":"Reviews","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/tone/reviews","apiUrl":"https://content.guardianapis.com/tone/reviews","references":[]},{"id":"type/article","type":"type","webTitle":"Article","webUrl":"https://www.theguardian.com/articles","apiUrl":"https://cont